{"type":"message","timestamp":"2026-07-19T02:27:55.454Z","session_id":"ses_087cc7187ffeZXjvwYcOSeYyUO","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Filed the issue on GitHub: https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues/791\n\nLearned standing requirement (create): Create a minimal Rust integration regression test at tests/issue_762.rs for issue 762. The missing feature is a distinct formal-ai with opencode-desktop target, separate from the existing opencode CLI. On Unix, create a fake desktop executable that captures arguments and environment. Invoke the formal-ai binary with: with --no-start-server --base-url http://127.0.0.1:18080 opencode-desktop. Set a proposed FORMAL_AI_OPENCODE_DESKTOP_BIN override to the fake executable so the test is portable. Assert the baseline currently fails because opencode-desktop is unsupported. Structure the final desired assertions so that once implemented it verifies: the fake native app launched; it received no CLI run or model arguments; FORMAL_AI_API_KEY is formal-ai-local; OPENCODE_CONFIG and OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR point to temporary isolated config; the JSON includes provider formalai using @ai-sdk/openai-compatible, baseURL http://127.0.0.1:18080/api/openai/v1, apiKey {env:FORMAL_AI_API_KEY}, model formalai/formal-ai; and the users ~/.config/opencode/opencode.json was not modified. Also add one global test proving with --global opencode-desktop merges that provider into ~/.config/opencode/opencode.json, creates a backup, with --undo restores the original byte-for-byte, and with --global --all reports opencode-desktop distinctly. Use different natural-language naming from issue 760 and keep the test self-contained. Run cargo test --test issue_762 and stop after capturing the expected red failure. Do not edit production code, docs, changelog, GitHub issues, or pull requests."}]}
